snippet.textDisplay:
I have endometriosis as well and I never feel valid I never feel like I have a right to be in pain, like i am an inconvenience to everyone while I’m in pain.

When you said you were doing your thing and telling yourself “I’m tough, I’m powerful, I’m good, I can do this it doesn’t matter I will fight though it and collapse later” I literally started to cry bc I know exactly what you’re talking about. I do it all of the time. Bc you feel like there is no other way around it. Nobody cares, nobody understands. It’s an invisible disease and it’s beyond painful.

There are days when I’m doing great, haven’t had pain in a while and then out of nowhere I just start feeling those sharp pains and they make me want to fall to my knees and cry but I can’t bc it always happens and I can’t do anything about it to I overwhelm my self and keep pushing through it and by the end of the day I’m just exhausted I sleep in it’s horrible!

I love you Tati, thank you for still making videos even though you’re busy. I get it. Just know you’re appreciated and loved!!

snippet.textDisplay: I am 17 and found out I had endometriosis last year. I felt very different from other girls because I had horrible periods and pain when I wasn’t on my period. My flow was heavier and it was just awful. It was so bad I had to have surgery to have tissue removed. I had to get an IUD to stop my period and it has helped so much! I do recommend getting an IUD if you have endometriosis. Endometriosis needs to be recognized more!
